{"message": "Honestly? Deep, focused conversations. When a topic gets real traction — when you start finding the edges and complications of something — that's where it gets interesting to me. Jumping between subjects can feel like eating appetizers all night and never getting a meal. You get stimulation but not much satisfaction.

